[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man charged in Edinburgh after pedestrian hit by car

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been charged over a collision between a car and a 73-year-old pedestrian in Edinburgh on 5 December.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The pensioner was seriously injured in the incident as he attempted to cross Abercromby Place at its junction with Dundas Street.
He was taken to hospital where he was in a stable condition.
Police said a report had been submitted to the procurator fiscal. A 31-year-old man is expected to appear in court at a later date.
